es not result in a majority for one candidate; the candidate who receives a plurality in the second round becomes president (there is no obligation for weaker candidates to drop out). The role of the president is mostly to represent Palestine, but he also has some crucial governing powers. The president and Prime_minister can together use emergency decrees to govern, bypassing the palestinian_council. The president can also appoint or remove a Prime_minister when a parliamentary majority is unable to be established, and can thus influence the formation of a government."},{"type":"paragraph","content":"Palestine is divided into a number of states, each of which have their own governments with some responsibilities. By far the largest and most important state is West Bank."}]},"main.party":{"id":"main.party","title":"Party Affairs","cardImage":"img/fatah.jpg","isDeck":true,"options":[{"id":"#party_affairs"}],"content":{"content":"","type":"paragraph"}},"root.start_menu_2":{"id":"root.start_menu_2","options":[{"id":"@root.start","title":"Start game"},{"id":"@election_simulation","title":"Election simulation"},{"id":"@credits","title":"Credits"},{"id":"@game_over.achievements"}],"content":{"content":"","type":"paragraph"}},"status.paramilitaries":{"id":"status.paramilitaries","onArrival":[{"$code":"if (Q.rb_strength) {
