Israel agreed to withdraw its military forces from parts of the Gaza Strip and the West Bank, beginning with Gaza and Jericho in 1994.Despite these steps, the Oslo process ultimately failed to achieve a lasting peace. The final status negotiations stalled, and the process was derailed by ongoing Israeli settlement expansion, which increased from 263,000 settlers in 1993 to 357,000 by 2000, in violation of commitments not to alter the status of the occupied territories."},{"type":"paragraph","content":{"type":"conditional","content":"Our foreign Minister Mustafa Barghouti has signed the treaty. The reaction is generally muted; both pacifists and militarists are skeptical about the efficacy of the treaty.","predicate":0}}],"stateDependencies":[{"type":"predicate","fn":{"$code":"return (Q['foreign_minister_party'] == "pni");"}}]},"countVisitsMax":1},"ppp_policy.labor_oppose":{"id":"ppp_policy.labor_oppose","onArrival":[{"$code":"Q['ppp_coalition_dissent'] = (Q['ppp_coalition_dissent'] || 0) + 1;
